column5: Beautiful cars Marko. Even though those Italian jobs are fast, snazzy and expensive my first choice would still be that nice bright red Mustang Cobra. Love the 'Stangs! even if the only one I ever had was a blue '67 that I only kept for a day before selling it to a buddy that rolled it at Port Dover. What a waste! It would be worth a fortune today just in parts alone.
wow some awesome looking cars!  but i wonder if some of those lambo's could tow a boat?  thanks for the pics!  cheers!
awesome pictorial series Marko!  By any chance were there any Maybach's there? did you snap a few pics?  G

Yes there was one and there must have been 100 people around it, i had to get up on the stand of other car just to even take a peek at it. It was practicly impossible to take a half decent picture.  Sorry man
